<module status="bronze">
    <h>suas</h>
    <p><g>suas</g>
        <en>[to] up there</en> is is a distal adverb of motion along a <a href="?q=motion"
            >trajectory</a> (contrasting with both the proximal <a href="?gd=a-nìos"
            ><g>a-nìos</g></a>
        <en>[to] up here</en> and the distal <a href="?gd=sìos"><g>sìos</g></a>
        <en>[to] down there</en>).</p>
    <section>
        <h>uses</h>
        <section>
            <h>complement</h>
            <module status="bronze" id="rach_suas">
                <h>rach suas</h>
                <p><g><a href="?gd=rach">rach</a> suas</g>
                    <en>go up(wards)</en> – <ul>
                        <li>pedagogical examples – <xl id="comps-suas-pedag">
                                <li>
                                    <gd>Tha Anna a’ dol <m>suas an staidhre</m>. | Chuala mi fuaim
                                        shuas an staidhre. Chaidh mi <m>suas</m>. </gd>
                                    <tr>Ann is going up the stairs. | I heard a noise upstairs. I
                                        went up. </tr>
                                    <ref text="609">td. 30, 39</ref>
                                </li>
                            </xl></li>
                    </ul></p>
            </module>
        </section>
    </section>

</module>
